          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best free SEO audit tool?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Google Search Console is the best free SEO audit tool for most websites. It shows indexing errors, Core Web Vitals issues, manual actions, and which queries are driving clicks. For technical crawl audits, Screaming Frog's free tier (up to 500 URLs) is the strongest free option beyond GSC.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How often should you run an SEO audit?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Run a technical audit quarterly. Check Google Search Console monthly for new indexing errors and Core Web Vitals regressions. Run a full content audit once per year to identify thin content, cannibalization, and pages worth consolidating. theStacc runs ongoing content audits as part of its publishing workflow.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much does a professional SEO audit cost?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Agency SEO audits run $1,500–$10,000 depending on site size and scope. Tool-based audits (Semrush, Ahrefs, SE Ranking) run $50–$250/month and give you the same crawl data that agencies use. theStacc includes an ongoing content health audit as part of its $99/month subscription.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What should an SEO audit include?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">A complete SEO audit covers: technical health (crawl errors, indexing, redirects, page speed, Core Web Vitals), on-page SEO (title tags, meta descriptions, heading structure, internal linking), content quality (thin pages, duplicate content, keyword cannibalization), backlink profile (lost links, toxic links), and local SEO (for local businesses: GBP completeness, citation consistency, review velocity).</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I do an SEO audit myself?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
